38:38.652 --> 38:40.494
And I've had the same thing about a library.

38:41.075 --> 38:42.257
It can't be comprehensive.

38:42.798 --> 38:44.100
It can't collect everything.

38:44.120 --> 38:44.380
All right.

38:44.630 --> 38:53.564
Well, that's interesting, because there is a point where you did make the leap from collector to scholar, it sounds to me.

38:53.604 --> 38:54.265
Not scholar.

38:54.605 --> 39:00.895
Making available stuff that I think, like I bought, I saw an auction.

39:00.975 --> 39:02.517
I bought children's theater material.

39:03.279 --> 39:04.260
Children's material?

39:04.280 --> 39:05.061
Theater material.

39:05.342 --> 39:12.072
Two publishers, their whole warehouses were being auctioned out in Sotheby's, and

39:12.659 --> 39:13.560
looked at the price.

39:13.780 --> 39:15.702
It was expensive.

39:15.822 --> 39:20.828
But I said, you know, telling stories is like reading stories.

39:21.108 --> 39:24.172
Before literature, there was the storyteller.

39:24.212 --> 39:25.493
There was the Homer.

39:25.513 --> 39:32.140
There was the word-of-mouth, the Slavic bards, etc., where for 600 years not a word was varied.

39:32.160 --> 39:34.162
The same is true in the Old Testament.

39:34.182 --> 39:39.028
That was handed down for probably 800 years without a word variant.

39:40.049 --> 39:41.130
And so the

39:41.448 --> 39:43.410
The Bard had a storytelling.

39:43.430 --> 39:48.716
It was a very strong and monotic type of thing.

39:49.277 --> 39:54.403
So I figured, and this was a dramatic type of thing, so I went and bid and bought it.

39:54.543 --> 39:55.905
Both two things.

39:55.925 --> 39:58.308
And I didn't want to hear, so I sent them to Princeton.

39:58.668 --> 40:01.872
When it came, they called me up and they asked, what did I do?

40:02.072 --> 40:09.421
Turns out it was seven tons of material.

40:09.441 --> 40:09.801
I love that.

40:10.000 --> 40:13.505
Were they appreciative?

40:13.545 --> 40:14.466
Not to.

40:15.347 --> 40:19.233
They had to put it down below in a concrete slab to hold the space, etc.

40:19.353 --> 40:20.455
I hadn't seen it.

40:21.055 --> 40:30.829
But what it does is someday a scholar is going to look at it and it will be important in a research thing, you know, scholarship.

40:31.790 --> 40:39.501
Right now I'm doing different looks at American history and how we look at American history

40:39.785 --> 40:47.538
Not so much through the dates, but through different issues and setting up courses that way and using some of the treatises that the children have.

